title: H.S. football: Defensive player of the year watch for Oct. 26, 2015
text:
H.S. football: Defensive player of the year watch for Oct. 26, 2015 October 26, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 26, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record 
Defensive Player of the Year watch 
Louis Acceus, St. Joseph, jr. LB 
Recorded 18 tackles, including one for a loss, in a 16-13 loss to Bergen Catholic in overtime. Has a team-high 71 tackles and four sacks in seven games. 
Joey Kenny, Wayne Hills, sr. LB 
Posted nine tackles, one for a loss, as the Patriots topped Paramus, 28-7. Is Wayne Hills’ leader with 72 tackles, including nine for losses and five sacks, through eight games. 
Jaysen Thompson, Hackensack, sr. LB 
Made a season-high 18 tackles (one for a loss), recorded a sack and forced two fumbles in the Comets’ come-from-behind, 28-27 win at Ridgewood. Leads Hackensack with 71 tackles (17 for losses) in six games. 
Isiah Tolbert, Passaic Tech, sr. DT 
Four of his seven tackles accounted for losses and he recorded a sack in the Bulldogs’ 19-7 win against Clifton. Through seven games, has 51 tackles (13 for losses), 4 1/2 sacks and three fumble recoveries. 
Joe Williams, Pascack Valley, sr. LB 
Produced 10 tackles, including two for losses and half a sack, and defended a pass during the Indians’ 35-6 defeat of Passaic Valley. Twenty-two of his team-leading 66 tackles have gone for losses and has 7 1/2 sacks in seven games. 
– Mark J. Czerwinski and Keith Idec
